WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:31.680 --> 00:00:35.660
Escaping personal or ideological abusive environments

00:00:35.660 --> 00:00:39.980
isn't always a straightforward matter of recognising the situation intellectually

00:00:39.980 --> 00:00:42.660
and making a logical exit plan.

00:00:43.180 --> 00:00:46.540
Sometimes, rational rocket thrust alone isn't enough.

00:00:47.460 --> 00:00:51.900
Our emotions play a huge part in our ability to navigate daily life,

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:58.620
and the distorted emotional responses drilled into us by relentless rehearsal in the abusive environment

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:02.460
can disrupt our functioning at the most subtle levels.

00:01:02.780 --> 00:01:06.260
With this important part of our navigation systems compromised,

00:01:06.260 --> 00:01:10.200
simple, everyday interactions can become a minefield

00:01:10.360 --> 00:01:13.560
of self-sabotaging thoughts and conflicted behaviour.

00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:17.360
Not only does this work to keep us stuck in our situation,

00:01:17.480 --> 00:01:21.720
it can act like a magnet to other abusive individuals and groups.

00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:26.540
So, even if we achieve escape velocity from one abusive environment,

00:01:26.540 --> 00:01:31.060
we might find ourselves repeatedly pulled into the orbit of new ones.

00:01:31.740 --> 00:01:35.840
People who've been subjected to different kinds of abusive environments

00:01:35.920 --> 00:01:40.900
often show highly convergent themes in their descriptions of their experiences.

00:01:41.540 --> 00:01:44.500
Years ago, when I began talking in depth

00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:49.480
with people who'd been recruited by religious and pseudoscientific high-control groups,

00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:56.660
hearing them recount their experiences was like hearing a gigantic tuning fork resonating at my own pitch.

00:01:57.020 --> 00:02:00.220
Their observations about life inside a high-control group

00:02:00.220 --> 00:02:05.420
echoed private observations I'd made about my life inside a narcissistic family.

00:02:05.740 --> 00:02:10.000
There was the same divisiveness, where loyalty to the dictatorship

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:13.580
came before any personal relationship between other members;

00:02:13.940 --> 00:02:16.300
the same social isolation tactics,

00:02:16.300 --> 00:02:20.620
trying to sabotage external relationships with friends or lovers,

00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:24.020
the same attempts to maintain child-like dependence.

00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:32.620
Parallels have repeatedly been noticed between scriptural tales of vengeful, dictatorial gods and abusive relationships,

00:02:32.620 --> 00:02:36.280
noting the same threat of dehumanising brutality,

00:02:36.280 --> 00:02:40.720
the same capriciousness generating erratic, inconsistent demands.

00:02:41.200 --> 00:02:46.680
the same sense of all-pervading invasion into every aspect of the target's life,

00:02:46.680 --> 00:02:49.080
with no boundaries and no privacy.

00:02:50.520 --> 00:02:57.200
The details of abuse vary from situation to situation, with different levels of intensity or sadism.

00:02:57.200 --> 00:03:00.560
but the essential underlying mechanics merge.

00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:07.700
At their core, all abusive environments are about gaining coercive control over others.

00:03:07.700 --> 00:03:12.860
So, it's not surprising that abusive individuals and groups of all kinds -

00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:18.980
religious, political, academic, familial, romantic -

00:03:18.980 --> 00:03:25.520
converge on the same manipulative tactics to get people to sacrifice their autonomy and authenticity,

00:03:25.520 --> 00:03:27.640
and submit to fixed roles.

00:03:28.440 --> 00:03:31.320
Not content with controlling their target's actions,

00:03:31.320 --> 00:03:34.660
many abusers also seek to dictate to their targets

00:03:34.660 --> 00:03:37.740
how they should feel about their enslavement.

00:03:37.740 --> 00:03:41.360
Having had so much of their existence scripted for them,

00:03:41.360 --> 00:03:46.120
targets of abuse repeatedly report feeling like actors on a stage,

00:03:46.120 --> 00:03:49.040
forced not only to perform tasks,

00:03:49.040 --> 00:03:53.140
but to perform characters created for them by their abusers,

00:03:53.140 --> 00:03:58.360
who take on the dual role of actor-director in their own production.

00:03:58.600 --> 00:04:01.480
And we're not talking Orson Welles.

00:04:01.480 --> 00:04:07.000
There's no depth, no emotional insight, no coherent motivation.

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:15.360
Not surprising, when you consider that the actor-director's psychological age is often still in single digits.

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:22.020
Certainly in the case of narcissistic abuse, we're looking at severely arrested development.

00:04:22.480 --> 00:04:28.200
Next time you see a child playing with toys, making them say and do things to each other,

00:04:28.620 --> 00:04:30.200
take a good look:

00:04:30.200 --> 00:04:33.660
you're watching a model of life with a narcissist.

00:04:33.660 --> 00:04:38.520
You're seeing the actor-director inventing characters and motivations,

00:04:38.520 --> 00:04:40.840
and controlling relationships.

00:04:41.440 --> 00:04:46.980
And, if you analyse the storylines, you'll find a good degree of projection going on.

00:04:47.540 --> 00:04:52.820
Children might punish their toys for being naughty, when they've been naughty themselves.

00:04:53.160 --> 00:05:03.280
In a similar way, adult narcissists repeatedly project their own flaws and transgressions onto their innocent toys: in this case, other human beings.

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:11.480
Just like toys, targets are directed to play nonsensical fragmented ciphers with no inner life.

00:05:11.480 --> 00:05:16.860
They exist as cartoonish props around the central figure of the abuser,

00:05:16.860 --> 00:05:19.980
who often presents as an unappreciated martyr.

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:29.760
Just like toys, their single function is to constantly affirm whatever persona their abuser chooses to adopt at any given time.

00:05:29.760 --> 00:05:36.080
There might be a succession of different personas, each catering to the abuser's ever-shifting needs.

00:05:36.080 --> 00:05:39.880
Each time, history can be reinvented.

00:05:39.880 --> 00:05:45.120
Leaders of religious high-control groups will update their old literature,

00:05:45.120 --> 00:05:47.980
editing out failed teachings and prophecies,

00:05:47.980 --> 00:05:54.420
erasing evidence of past blunders to try and maintain a mask of impenetrable perfection.

00:05:54.420 --> 00:05:59.280
Targets are expected to treat the new script as if it always existed.

00:05:59.280 --> 00:06:02.480
Fleeting expressions of confusion might be allowed,

00:06:02.500 --> 00:06:09.860
if they're swiftly followed by performances of cheerful acceptance when bogus justifications are supplied.

00:06:09.860 --> 00:06:16.400
But extended displays of sincere, unresolved confusion aren't tolerated.

00:06:16.400 --> 00:06:22.920
Actors who break character unsettle the group and risk ruining the theatrical production.

00:06:22.920 --> 00:06:28.080
The targets, being repeatedly forced to perform emotions they don't feel,

00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:33.360
or, deny the emotions they *do* feel, is a profoundly self-negating act.

00:06:33.360 --> 00:06:39.800
Treating emotions as mere performances to be selected according to whether they please an audience

00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:43.760
is a complete perversion of their function as survival tools

00:06:43.760 --> 00:06:46.480
that help us process our experiences.

00:06:46.480 --> 00:06:52.540
The psychological burden of managing this disparity between reality and performance

00:06:52.540 --> 00:06:57.640
can distort and sometimes obliterate our entire emotional landscape.

