00:07:05.840 --> 00:07:11.700
Emotions can feel wildly volatile and overwhelming to very young children.

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:19.040
With the help of healthy reflection, and healthy modeling, they can come to recognise and manage them.

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:26.300
Children learn about their feelings when their emotional expressions are consistently and reliably identified

00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:30.720
and, reflected back in the responses of the people around them.

00:07:30.720 --> 00:07:38.980
Children also learn by example from seeing the people around them modelling emotional responses appropriate to the situation,

00:07:38.980 --> 00:07:41.660
and, resolving them in healthy ways.

00:07:41.660 --> 00:07:47.460
We develop volume dials distinguishing different shades of emotional intensity.

00:07:47.480 --> 00:07:54.620
So, instead of suddenly flipping into immobilising terror in response to everything from mild to extreme threat,

00:07:54.620 --> 00:07:57.040
we respond in proportion to threat,

00:07:57.040 --> 00:08:03.380
moving from feeling unsettled, to vigilant, to afraid, to terrified.

00:08:03.380 --> 00:08:06.880
We start appreciating emotional combinations,

00:08:06.880 --> 00:08:12.200
like feeling sadness and anger at the same time, or, sadness and joy.

00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:16.100
As our emotional vocabulary becomes more nuanced and refined,

00:08:16.100 --> 00:08:19.700
our feelings become more closely aligned with our experiences

00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:25.240
which allows us to engage more effectively with the people and situations we encounter,

00:08:25.240 --> 00:08:31.620
motivating us to avoid danger, exercise self care, and pursue fulfilling goals.

00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:39.400
In contrast, children born into abusive environments experience all kinds of emotional neglect and chaos.

00:08:39.400 --> 00:08:45.500
Their emotional expressions might be habitually ignored, misread, or, punished.

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:49.300
Instead of having their feelings understood and attended to,

00:08:49.300 --> 00:08:54.020
young children might be expected to understand and attend to the feelings of their abusers,

00:08:54.020 --> 00:08:58.840
who exhibit emotional responses wildly out of sync with the situation.

00:08:58.840 --> 00:09:05.420
These children are crushed under emotional burdens they're not remotely equipped to handle.

00:09:05.420 --> 00:09:12.260
Instead of a baseline of emotional neutrality, the child might develop a baseline of active anxiety.

00:09:12.260 --> 00:09:15.580
Just a few dominant emotions might be recognised,

00:09:15.580 --> 00:09:18.240
while the rest are suppressed or distorted.

00:09:18.240 --> 00:09:22.240
If the pursuit of personal happiness is condemned as selfish,

00:09:22.240 --> 00:09:24.840
it might become merged with guilt.

00:09:24.840 --> 00:09:30.200
If anger is forbidden, the child might substitute anger with tearfulness.

00:09:30.200 --> 00:09:35.480
These kinds of distortions can create extreme emotional dysregulation,

00:09:35.480 --> 00:09:39.580
and overload the child with unmanageable feelings.

00:09:39.580 --> 00:09:44.140
On the flip side, the child might experience a flattening of affect,

00:09:44.140 --> 00:09:46.960
where the emotions shut down completely.

00:09:46.960 --> 00:09:48.680
The system breaks.

00:09:48.760 --> 00:09:50.860
The spark is snuffed out.

00:09:50.860 --> 00:09:57.660
The individual becomes a cold, analytic spectator, untouched, and unmoved.

00:09:57.660 --> 00:10:02.700
All of this turmoil and destruction is invisible to abusers,

00:10:02.700 --> 00:10:08.700
who view targets as playthings, and expect instant, fully-formed emotional responses,

00:10:08.700 --> 00:10:12.520
tailor made to fit the abuser's own needs.

00:10:12.660 --> 00:10:16.880
One of the ironies of coercing targets into performing false emotions

00:10:16.880 --> 00:10:22.140
is that their abusers are often aware that these performances aren't real.

00:10:22.140 --> 00:10:24.460
Abusers might lack empathy,

00:10:24.460 --> 00:10:28.440
but it doesn't mean they're unable to accurately gauge emotion.

00:10:28.440 --> 00:10:33.020
Their lack of empathy just reflects the fact that their targets' emotions only have value

00:10:33.020 --> 00:10:35.320
if they serve the abuser's needs.

00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:40.600
Abusers can be extremely perceptive regarding the authenticity of emotion.

00:10:40.600 --> 00:10:43.780
picking up on the tiniest conflicting cues.

00:10:43.780 --> 00:10:48.680
And targets are often repeatedly tested to assess their authenticity.

00:10:48.680 --> 00:10:53.220
Of course, abusers won't tolerate being tested themselves.

00:10:53.220 --> 00:10:57.600
If they realise their targets are performing false emotions,

00:10:57.600 --> 00:11:01.460
the emotional payoff the abusers are seeking is lost.

00:11:01.460 --> 00:11:04.260
They want to eat their cake and have it.

00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:08.740
They want to direct someone to feel the specific emotions they decide,

00:11:08.740 --> 00:11:12.960
but also want those emotions to be spontaneous and real.

00:11:12.960 --> 00:11:15.040
They can't have both.

00:11:15.040 --> 00:11:19.880
In trying to have both, they become the source of their own frustration.

00:11:19.880 --> 00:11:24.560
Another irony is that of course, these abusers are performing, too.

00:11:24.560 --> 00:11:30.660
The perfect image they hope to present to the world is just a cardboard cutout of a functioning adult,

00:11:30.660 --> 00:11:38.400
behind which often hides a child, constantly overwhelmed with rage, fear, and shame.

00:11:38.400 --> 00:11:44.820
They demand true emotions from others in order to sustain their own false self.

00:11:44.820 --> 00:11:48.480
What we have is a process of self replication.

00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:52.380
Abusers who are split into an emotionally-dysregulated hidden self,

00:11:52.380 --> 00:11:54.280
and a false-performing self,

00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:57.480
act in such a way as to split the people around them

00:11:57.480 --> 00:12:02.680
into emotionally-dysregulated hidden selves and false-performing selves.

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:08.000
The extent to which targets lose themselves in in their abuser's theatrical production

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:10.480
will depend on various factors

00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:12.940
including an intensity of abuse,

00:12:12.940 --> 00:12:15.280
presence or absence of support,

00:12:15.280 --> 00:12:20.220
the resilience and adaptiveness of the target's psychological defences,

00:12:20.220 --> 00:12:25.880
and, the ability of targets to fully acknowledge the tyranny in their midst.

